Also in 2014, a number of changes were made aimed at transforming the working and rest conditions of workers: New Year's corporate parties were banned at the expense of the enterprise, the library with more than 600 thousand volumes was liquidated (part of the book fund was transferred to a local college), showers and toilets were repaired through the sale of corporate foreign cars and locker rooms, as well as it is forbidden to keep indoor flowers in office premises[43]. margin, which raises doubts about the economic efficiency of the business as such. Losses were financed by attracting additional loans.